<bug>
	<id>338802</id>
	<title>XML perspective: in Graphical Layout, in the Properties view, the button to add a property doesn't work and text disappears</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Build Identifier: 20100917-0705</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">When I'm in the XML Perspective, editing a layout XML file, I can see each property in the properties view.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">I want to enter a value in a property, but the button that should open a popup with multiple choises (for example in the "layout_gravity" property, I should see a popup with tickables values like "center", "left", "horizontal_center", etc, like under Win 7) simply doesn't work.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">It does nothing at all.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.4">When I manually insert a value in a field, and hit the Enter button to confirm it, this value disappears, and it reappears only when i click on the value field again.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.2">1 in the XML Perspective, editing an XML layout file</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.3">2 click on a View or any other item</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.4">3 click the button in a value field</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
